I have a couple of coments and suggestions:
	1) You wanted to be able to animate the flow w/o having to press 
the buttons.  I think it's a great idea but i think that you should still 
be able to use the buttons to move the flow beat by beat.

	2) I don't know how difficult this would be for you but since you 
wanted to be able to animate the same show from either the alumni or 
student side, you could change the demension of how the step sizes work 
in order to get a better feel for what it would look like from an angle.  
North/south is fine but the east/west dimensions are compressed from the 
angle of the press and student sides.  Maybee if you have the dots 
marching 2 by 4 rectangles instead or marching in 2 by 2 squares like how 
the old calchart does it now.  Maybee charters will be able to get a 
better feel for how flows will look like at an angle if you do this.

	3) I may be just going off on this.  But if you can do that maybe 
you could also change the dimensions of the east west spacing.  From the 
angle of the press box the east west spacing is larger closer to the 
sidelines, and virtually vanishes as you move further away.  I don't now 
how much work it would take, but it would give us a better feel for how 
things will look.

I don't know if I got what I wanted to suggest to you conveyed to you 
right, so if you have any questions email me back.



Neil

