In the interests of "unification," I've been trying to reduce the concept
of "stuntsheet" and of "reference pt" into an expression of a certain
relationship of groups.  For this, I've been tinkering slightly with our
definition of group, but I don't quite have it right yet.  However, I'm
getting closer and closer, and I have a feeling that soon it will all
become crystal-clear.  I want to figure this out before I write any more
of the outline, so that's why I've stalled recently.

The really cool thing about reducing a stuntsheet to the level of any
other group is that all of the moving routines that we've designed will
then be applicable in a natural way to other groups.  This is already the
case with refpts, but I want to generalize, just to see where it will take us.

Dan


