interfaces that helps out.

I definitely agree that X and O are bad choices, but I couldn't think of
anything else.

I kind of like the idea that the program could run fully functionally
without the mouse.  One of these years, the band is probably going to get
a laptop.  Imagine we're in Pasadena rehearsing for the Rose Bowl, and
stunt realizes that there is a major mistake on one of the sheets.  They
could make new stuntsheets that evening on the laptop, print them at
Kinko's, and distribute them the next morning.  So, it might end up being
very useful to have some independence from specific pieces of hardware.

However, I respect the fact that you've got to write the actual code, so
our final decision should chiefly depend on what you think is feasible.

