Does the printing program run under X?  If so, can you send me a uuencoded
copy, or put a readable copy in your soda directory so that I can grab it
and ftp?

The "black hole" flow is an important lesson for us calchart designers. 
It is simply impossible to think of everything beforehand.  I guess there
should be an "enlarge" option (and shrink, too!) in the print routine. 
It's never been needed before, and it may never be needed again, but for
the sake of completeness I think it should be included. 
 
> Well, it's probably too late now, as I believe the poopsheets have gone 
> to the printer, but I'll keep this in mind for next year.  The reason 
> it's like that is just because it was sort of left over from the standard 
> printing mode when I converted stuff for spring show.

I mentioned in the outline that there could be high school football and
professional football printing also.  This would be very easy to implement
since only the hashes would need to be changed.
 
> Exactly.  But the trouble is that the flow isn't very impressive, 
> especially for all the collisions and other potential problems.  At least 
> it will be fun to watch (for me).

Well, that's what Spring Show is really all about.  It's a big excuse for
newly elected and selected structure members to show off all of their
supremely wonderful power.  "Stunt can chart any flow we damn well please,
and there's nothing you can do about it!"  Soon enough, their great moral
committments to innovation and experimentation will wear thin, and then
they will go back to simple-minded NSEW NP.  

I think you can tell that I don't have a lot of respect in general for
structure members.  That's because I witnessed so many silly things happen
from the position of an "underling."  I was quite unusual among underlings in
that I actually knew what was going on and was clueful enough to realize
that mistakes were being made.  I generally believe that almost all people
are involved in structure for the wrong reasons.  Even if they don't
realize it or admit it to themselves, they are after power.  Rune and Erin
are certainly that way, but I think that Dick is an exception.
 
> They have found a few basses and percussion players.  I believe they put 
> them on the outside (I was at part of the stunt meeting when they 
> selected the block because I was helping them with the poopsheets).

I noticed only 40 bandsmen in the block.  Does this mean that the incredible
lameness of spring show is finally becoming generally realized by the band
at large?
 
> Okay, time to start some major code writing.  Hopefully, I'll have 
> something to mail to you in a few weeks.

Keep me posted on progress.  I assume you will run into stumbling blocks
along the way and will have to make changes to the plan.

Dan


