At first, it seemed like you had done some very illogical things with the
user interface.  But then I realized that this is essentially a very
primitive version of the full Calchart program, so it makes sense.

There is some trouble with the sizing of the popup windows when the main
calchart window is particularly narrow or short.  it seems that the size
of the popup window is determined by ratio to the size of the whole
window.  thus, important text gets cut off when the main window is small
horizontally or vertically, and the popup window is unnecessarily large
when the main window is large horizontally or vertically.

I assume that the + and - icons have no purpose yet.  For what are they
meant to be used?

Obviously, key commands are sorely needed.  Just in the process of
testing, I was already tired of constantly using the pulldown menus.

The Pick Stuntsheets... option in the print popup window just gives an
empty window.  I assume that this means that you haven't yet installed a
way to just print some stuntsheets.  So, I owe stunt an apology for the
comments I made about them not knowing how to print out only some sheets,
since right now that is impossible.

I don't entirely like the way that files are chosen under the Open
command.  It would be nice to doubleclick a file to load it without having
to click on Ok.  Also, I think it would be better to require double
clicking (or click and then Ok) to enter a new directory.

Having to choose the .mas file is rather a pain in the ass.  Will this no
longer be a problem with your new file format.  If it still is a problem,
how about installing a method by which the program can detect that a
subdirectory is dedicated to a single show?  Use a special color to make
them stand out.  When you select that subdirectory, instead of displaying
contents, the show which it contains will be loaded immediately.

Dan


