> 
> Do you think so?  It does copy the current sheet after all (for the most 
> part).  But the old version does say insert...

I guess I'm just old-fashioned.  I think of it as "inserting" a sheet 
because that's what we used to call it, but others might of it as 
"copying" a sheet.  Here's another possibility: "New sheet before" and 
"New sheet after".
 
> > 15) Blockmoves should not snap all the men to grid, just the "leading" man.
> 
> Hmm, this is something you can't really do with the old version, but it 
> does seem much more useful this way.

This is one of the most significant mistakes in version 2.  By mistake, I 
mean something that works wrong as opposed to something that just wasn't 
implemented at all.
 
> > 17) Your convention is to show the zeroth beat of a sheet as opposed to
> > showing the 16th (or whateverth) beat of a sheet.  I think this makes sense
> > because it agrees with the way that musicians talk about beats.  However,
> > it is a change from the conventions of version 2.  I'm just pointing out
> > the difference and that your convention really is an arbitrary decision.
> 
> I know it's different, but I've heard other people complain about that 
> numbering, since it's a little different than the way we count when we're 
> marching.

I agree; your way is correct.
 
> Now, about editing continuity.  I've realized something that need to be 
