> 
> We're basically in agreement (although I was figuring this out as I was 
> writing).  The question I have left is this:
> 
> You create a new sheet, so all the people are plain.  You then create a 
> new continuity, say SPECIAL, and assign all people to it.  PLAIN gets 
> deleted because it's empty and not used.  What if the user decides to 
> have a group have PLAIN continuity again?  Under this system the user 
> could either create a new continuity or set the group's symbol to plain.  
> This seems okay to me, but what do you think?

The way I imagine it is that the user will have to select "New 
Continuity" and type "PLAIN" when the program asks for the name of the 
new continuity.

If you just reselect the points to be plain, the PLAIN continuity will NOT 
be created because the continuity group of the selected points will 
not change to PLAIN because the autocontinuity function does not apply in 
this case.  The reason is that the continuity group (SPECIAL) does not 
match the symbols of the affected men.

The autocontinuity function works as follows.  Recall that if a man's
continuity group matches his symbol, then his continuity group will be
changed automatically when his symbol is changed.  Otherwise, it will stay
the same under symbol changes. 

Dan


