Once the files are on the network I would think that we should set up
a "group" area for calchart.  This would have the (to most everyone)
path of
	H:\CALBAND\CALCHART
Under this could be subdirectories of 1994, 1995, 1996, PUBLIC, etc.
1994 and 1995 would be READ ONLY for everyone, 1996 would be READ ONLY
for most people, but Stunt and ADM-Poop would have write/create access,
and PUBLIC would have open access for everyone.  Then everyone could
see the shows, Stunt and Adm-Poop could do their jobs, everyone could
play around, and if people needed privacy they could save their
stuff into their own private directory somewhere else...

Does this sound workable?

> -Gurk

