> to have it called .ini and then be in a different format.  Someday I 

Exactly.
[...]
> Sounds good, but doesn't H: depend on what structure positions a person 
> is on?

No, currently H: does not depend on what structure position someone
is in.  Under the old system it did, and there were up to 4 drives
for up to four structure positions and there had to be priorities
among those and...  The new system is:  G:\ is for primary structure
position, H:\ is the root of the structure ("Groups") area and
whatever you have permissions for you can see there.

Much, much, much simpler to implement, easier for people to talk about
files (if you have a path/file name on the H: drive it's the same
for anyone on the SMA network), etc.

Of course, this may not mean anything after Xmas break when we move
to Win95 or to WinNT, but I don't know too much about that yet...

> -Gurk

Rune


