A few times (maybe three times in three years), I encountered a bug that 
I was never able to reproduce.  I never figured out exactly what was 
causing it, and I don't remember precisely how I fixed it.  However, the 
symptoms sound the same, so it is probably the same bug.

What I DO remember is....  One of the stuntsheet files (*.s*) or one of 
the continuity files (*.f* [Historical note: the "f" stands for "forms", 
which was Martin's original not-so-good term for continuity]) got messed 
up somehow, and that was causing all the trouble when you accessed the 
file by animating or viewing the stuntsheet.

To fix the problem, I THINK that I figured out which file was bad, then I 
erased that file, renamed all of the higher numbered files, and edited 
the *.mas file manually (it is just a text file, so use any editor) to 
reduce the number of sheets.  So you lose one sheet, but you save 
everything else.

Gurk gets what I'm talking about, and probably Rune, too.  I'm not 
certain that this is the right thing to do, so make a copy of what you've 
got before you try.

Dan



