> concern about "rows or columns" is a good indication of the problem.  Of
> course, there is no reason to say that rows come before columns or columns
> come before rows; it depends on the orientation of the flow.  If you make 
> one the default, it will be completely arbitrary and half the time will 
> be completely wrong.
> 
