This discussion came up as long ago as 1991.  Karla Orosco thought that 
Martin could sell his program.  I'm not convinced that it would be very 
useful to anybody but that one weird school from the East Bay that hired 
the TAs to teach them how to march.  And maybe the band at UC Davis.  Do 
you know any other bands that march primarily in straight lines?

In 1991 or 1992, we got a demo video tape from a company selling charting
software for Macintoshes.  It had lots of features and would have been
very useful for us if we marched corps-style.  I don't remember too much
about it, but this is how it basically worked.  You put in a curve
(splined along several points?) and told the program how many people ought
to be on the curve.  It located them automatically by evenly spacing them. 
The animation was primarily even steps direct-to-position, which is how
corps-style bands march. 

I don't remember the name of the company or the price or anything like 
that.  Maybe the drum major file cabinet (or the AV comm cabinet) still 
has the video and literature.

Dan



