X-Status: 


I attended a rather large high school marching band competition this 
weekend at the Hoosier^H^H^H^H^H^H^HRCA Dome in Indianapolis.  There were 
80 bands from all over the Midwest and a few from elsewhere.  All of the 
ten bands I saw marched the typical paisley/amoeba/rotating box drills 
accompanied by the typical non-melodic modern music.

The point is that the program of the show contained a half page
advertisement for Macintosh platform show design software.  The ad
mentioned several features such as animation and a point-and-click
interface. 

Some other aspects described were particularly useful for the typical high
school/drum corps style shows and not very doable with Calchart.  For
example, the main data units are not individual men but rather lines
(curved or straight).  You tell the program how many men to put on the
line, and it evenly spaces them along it.  This gives great flexibility in
the number of men in the show, which is extremely useful for drum corps
but rather difficult with Calchart. 

The name of the company is Advanced Technologies, and their phone number 
is +1 800 348 5003.  They advertised that they can send demos, so someone 
might want to call them.

Dan


