On Wed, 20 Aug 1997, Dan Isaksen wrote:

> I believe that in effect EVEN NP REM was the default continuity in v.2.
> Probably it was not implemented internally that way because Martin
> probably wrote the default continuity routine before the continuity
> language was finalized.

I maybe it did something like, if it's a straight line to NP, do FMTO NP, 
MTRM.

> Your question is a good one.  After writing about 20 lines of text on the
> issue, I just deleted it all and figured out a much better solution.  I
> believe that it takes care of all your concerns in a consistent and
> logical way.
> 
> I agree with your suggestion that there should be a way to indicate that a
> sheet should be ignored for the purposes of animation.  
> 
> I sometimes used to input all the sheets before writing any of the
> continuity.  I could flip through the animation quickly and misplaced men
> would often show up easily.  So the default for each sheet should be
> animation inclusion.
> 
> My suggestion avoids the Stunt-confusing inconsistency of turning 0 beats
> into 1 beat.  The default number of beats for a sheet should be 1 beat. 
> Then 1 beat really means one beat.  The user can indicate that a sheet
> should be excluded from animation by manually setting the number of beats
> to 0.
> 
> This has the advantage of being less mysterious - the program is doing
> what it says - 1 beat for 1 beat, not 1 beat for 0 beats.  Also, it avoids
> the need for implementing yet another feature on the pulldown menus, which
> I always like to avoid.  And I just think that the solution is logical in
> general: 0 beats really should mean that you skip.
> 
> The problem of 0 beats vs 1 beats is related to the question of whether NP
> is reached on beat 32 of the current sheet or not until beat 1 of the
> following sheet.  This issue was never thoroughly resolved in v.2.  I
> remember that it caused some confusion with music integration because beat
> 1 musically speaking was not always beat 1 in terms of animation. 
> Musically speaking, NP should be reached on beat 1 of the following sheet. 
> 
> The default of 1 beat will also take care of some funny things that used
> to happen on the last page of a show.

I really like this approach.  The problem is with backwards 
compatibility.  I think it's unlikely that there's a sheet in the middle 
of a show with zero beats, but it could mess things up when NP refers to 
a different sheet.  I think the best way to get around this is to change 
all zeros to ones for shows done with version 2.  That also gets around 
the problem of the last sheet having zero beats when it was intended to 
be shown.

But what do you do if you refer to NP when the only following sheets have 
zero beats?  That should be an error, right?  I think I currently have NP 
on the last sheet defined as the starting position on that sheet.

In my version, NP is reached on beat 1 of the next sheet.  The first beat 
of animation (the hup) is labeled as zero.  But what should happen if 
there's animation on the last sheet?  Should it add a beat, or give an 
error?  That would solve the NP problem if animation isn't allowed.  I 
believe there are times when Stunt has done that... say you have a block 
do 8N, 8E, 8S, 8W... an extra stuntsheet at the end isn't really needed.

Gurk


From gmeeker@cantina Thu Aug 21 13:48:39 1997
