From: Garrick Meeker <gmeeker@cantina>
To: dci@math.uchicago.edu
cc: Garrick Meeker <gmeeker@cantina>
Subject: CalChart trivia
Message-ID: <Pine.SOL.3.91.970821133943.432A-100000@cantina>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII
Content-Length: 649
Status: RO
X-Status: 

I began testing the new calchart last night by animating the old shows.  
I hadn't had many problems with recent shows, but then I started testing 
shows from '90.  I found all sorts of discrepencies/bugs.  For instance, 
the step command didn't use DM distances (this isn't actually documented, 
but it's the right thing to do.)  Lots of things like that.  It's also 
good to test some of the more obscure commands (like FOUNTAIN, OPP, etc., 
and things like variables) but these have actually held up so far.  It 
really pointed out the differences between the way you and stunt think 
about continuity.  Just thought you'd like to know...

Gurk


