First I have some questions about how some features work.


What do all the different colors mean during animation?

Is there a way to do additive blocking?  I have forgotten.

Do the middle and right buttons have any function other than polygonal and
lasso blocking?

What exactly are all the purposes of the shift, control, alt, etc. keys?

If you call the individual move icon the "first" and start counting to the
right, I can't figure out what the fourth and sixth icons are for.  Are
they the ones that aren't installed yet?



Now here are some complaints I have about the user interface.


Rotation move is virtually useless as it is.  It is impossible to get a
line to rotate exactly 90 degrees for example, because the angle choice is
"continuous".  There should be some discreteness so that exact angles can
be obtained.  For example, as you drag the mouse around, the location of
the cursor should jump from grid point to grid point (rather than
continuously) so that the angle also jumps.  If you want very fine angles,
you can go to a long radius where the choices are closer together.  I fear
that I have explained this poorly.  I'll try again if you don't
understand.

I hate having to select individual move if I want to reblock.  There
should be a way to block while having another move selected.  Or better
the individual move should automatically be reselected after each
geniusmove.  It is unlikely that someone will want to do the same kind of
move to the exact same set of men twice in a row.  In general, either you
are going to select a new block or you are going to select another kind of
move.

I am still not convinced that smartmove is of much use.  But we've had
this argument before.

There is no way (at least, not that I could find) to make arbitrarily
named continuity groups.  This is important in many situations, such as
dividing the band into two groups north and south of the 50.


So far I have only found two bugs.  Both of them caused the whole program
to crash.  I've copied the error messages for you.

Closing the Setup Show window after setting number of points causes crash.

X Error:  BadPixmap
  Request Major code 54 ()
  ResourceID 0x2fb860
  Error Serial #5696
  Current Serial #5735

While reanimating, the program crashed.

X Error:  BadPixmap
  Request Major code 54 ()
  ResourceID 0x2ff960
  Error Serial #76433
  Current Serial #76461


