> 
> I'm pretty sure that all of your transformations are just special cases of
> a general affine transformation.  Tell me exactly how you think that
> chevrons can be turned into parallel lines.  A single chevron to a single
> line can already be done with geniusmove, but if you try to do several
> nesting chevrons, you get into trouble.

Suppose you have a formation like:

   *     *     *     *
  * *   * *   * *   * *
 *   * *   * *   * *   *
*     *     *     *     *

If you want to turn this into a line, you could use the scale
transformation and drag a peak into a line.  If you have a ref point p0,
you start dragging at p1, and end at p2, the scale factor for y is
(p2y-p0y)/(p1y-p0y) which is 0.  So the matrix would be (ignoring
translation components):

| 1 0 0 |
| 0 0 0 |
| 0 0 0 |

Which you definately couldn't do with regular genius move.  Right?

As for the animation colors, I couldn't get a scheme I like.  You can edit
runtime/config yourself to experiment.  The lines to edit should be
obvious.  You can change the color names to three integers (0-255 for the
red, green, and blue components).  The values for the normal ones are
something like:

255 255 255 : White
255 255   0 : Yellow
135 205 235 : Sky blue

You can try darker colors:

190 190 190
190 190   0
100 152 175

Or maybe complements:

  0   0   0  (unfortunely the complement of white is really white)
  0   0 255
121  50  20

I'm thinking that maybe all directions should be one obvious color, like
red.  Let me know what you think.

Gurk



