Funny that you should mention a block smartmove.  The way I invented 
geniusmoves was by trying to generalize smartmoves to blocks.  I recall
pursuing the idea in some depth.  We were thinking of using one button to
place the next point along the line (like a regular smartmove) and another
button to place the next point in the next column.  But it never made
much sense and didn't seem flexible enough to be useful, so we dropped the
idea.  

