> I was looking through old messages, and I was wondering about this.
> What direction should things be facing?  Should everyone face the same
> direction, so that they move backwards, or should they face the direction
> they're traveling?  I would think that the first method would be correct.
> What if you give a direction to face for MARCH?  Should everyone face the
> opposite direction if the beats are negative?

I was looking through old messages, and I realized that I never responded
to this.  I think that negative beats should only affect the direction of
travel, not the direction you are facing.  So a command like MARCH HS -8 N
means go south, but face north.  And a command like MARCH HS -8 N W (I'm
not sure of the syntax here) means go south but face west.

Dan




