Here are some comments on the 12/2/97 version.  I expect to have time over
the next two weeks for a significant amount of testing.


At first, the new scrolling method confused me.  It felt like the field
was moving the wrong way when I moved the mouse.  That's because I had the
wrong mental picture of the situation.  You are thinking that scrolling
moves the field around, while the window is fixed.  I was thinking that
the field is fixed, but you move the window around over it.  It doesn't
need changing; fine how it is.

The control key will be used a lot.  Isn't it better to assign a mouse
button to the scrolling function?  Take whatever function that button had,
and put it on the control key.

Have you tried blockmoving points across the field?  It is a bit tricky
because you have to hold the shift key continuously while holding and
releasing the control key several times.  Using a mouse button instead of
control will make it a bit easier.

After blocking a bunch of points in preparation for a smartmove, I forgot
to click on the smartmove icon.  So the program thought I was doing an
individualmove; this had no effect, except that the blocked points became
unblocked.  Undo didn't help because it didn't consider that effectless
individualmove as an edit.  I had to reblock everything.  There should be
a way to recover the most recent block, or something like that. 

DOF is undefined at the beginning of a sheet.  I thought we had discussed
borrowing the value from the previous sheet.  This would still be
undefined on the first sheet.  When DOF is undefined, the error message is
"Undefined value" with no reference to DOF or even a line number; that's
too terse to be of much help. 

After MARCH HS 8 N E, DOF equals E.  Should it equal E, or should it equal
N?  I think E is correct, but I just wanted to point out that there is
something to think about here.  Maybe there should be another variable DOM
(Direction Of Motion).

Dan


