I don't recall whether I already wrote to you about this problem.
Animation, setup, and continuity windows are associated to particular main
windows.  If you're viewing more than one show, it is important to know
which window is associated with which show.  There should be names on the
title bars of the windows.

After deleting a sheet, the sheet bar gets confused.  I had two
stuntsheets, and I deleted the second one.  The viewer returned to the
first sheet, but the bar was stuck on 2.  It was shaded, and I couldn't
move it until I created a new sheet. [I'm proud of this one; somewhat
obscure problem.]

Currently the default name for a new sheet is the same as the name from
the sheet copied.  There should be a smarter system.  If a sheet is added
at the end of a show and the old last sheet's name is a number n, then the
new sheet name should be n+1.  If a sheet is added at the beginning and
the old first sheet's name is a number n, then the new sheet name should
be n-1.  If a sheet is added in the middle and the sheets on either side
are n and n+1, then the new sheet should be nA.  Now that I think about
it, replace "number" by "number possibly followed by a single letter".
In all other cases, leave the sheet name blank.  It is better to have no
name than to have the same name as another sheet; two sheets with the same
name is confusing.

In case I'm not being clear, here are some examples.  Add a stuntsheet
before the first sheet, which is labeled "1"; the new name is "0".  Add a
stuntsheet after the last sheet, which is labeled "32A"; the new name is
"33".  Add a sheet between "16B" and "17"; the new sheet is "16C".  Add a
new sheet between "16" and "17B"; the new sheet is "16A".  Add a new sheet
between "16B" and "16C"; the new sheet gets no name.

Automatically delete continuity groups that have standard names (plain,
solid, etc.) and that have no text and that have no points assigned to
them.

When you reanimated with collision checking on, the points show up purple.
Once you view the animation, they go to the correct color.  If you back up
to the first beat, they are the correct color.  It only happens right
after you reanimate.

Dan




