On Sat, 20 Dec 1997, Dan Isaksen wrote:

> 
> What is Relabel sheets supposed to do?  I figured it was supposed to
> change the sheet titles, but it doesn't seem to have that effect.  In
> fact, it doesn't seem to have any effect.

It's like Hook, but it doesn't append a show.  It tries to match the
formation on the current sheet to the next sheet and relabels all the
following sheets.  This was from my own wish list.

> I'd like to be able to snap points to the grid.

I know.  It's on the list.

> Why is Edit printed continuity under the Animation menu?  It goes with
> Edit continuity, and Edit continuity goes with Animation, but "goes with"
> is not transitive.

I'm was thinking.  I'll move it.  The Edit menu is getting big though.

> You will be happy to hear that I have been playing with Undo quite a bit.
> I made a list of all the things that I could find that are undoable.  They
> are
> 
>   append sheets
>   copy stuntsheet
>   delete stuntsheet
>   movement
>   edit show description
>   change stuntsheet name
>   set number of beats
>   label location
>   symbol change
>   continuity assignment
>   edit continuity.
> 
> Have I missed any?

I think changing the labels names in the information window is also
undoable.  The only things that should not be undoable are changing the
number of points and the relabel option.  These could be undoable, but
they make such significant changes that I didn't bother.

> When does a continuity edit become undoable?  Only after an animation?
> That doesn't seem frequent enough for me.  Certainly it is not necessary
> to undo every keystroke.  However, it makes some sense to allow for an
> undo as soon as some other action (other than keystrokes to the continuity
> editor) is done.
> 
> If I do a null movement, I can't undo it (which is correct).  But if I do
> a null label change or continuity assignment or symbol change, then the
> null action is undoable.

Yeah, I should fix that.

> There should be some sort of undoing for blocking.  Already several
> time I have regretted having to start from the beginning.

Something like "Get last selection".  There's also the idea of creating
selection groups like percussion, basses, TAs, etc.

> After relabeling sheets (an undoable action), the undo buffer is cleared.
> This isn't really necessary, is it?  If I did a movement just before
> relabeling, why can't I undo that movement after relabeling?  I
> guess this might be a problem for undoing title changes.  

You might already see why now, but the problem is that relabeling is not
undoable but it moves points.  If you keep the undo buffer, you could get
some weirdness happening as you undo movements.

Gurk



