- Remove mention of undefined reference points from manual
- Keyboard shortcuts
- Yardline ruler (to display yardlines at all times)
- View multiple reference sheets
- Handle negative beats (COUNTERMARCH, EVEN, FM, HSCM, MARCH, MT, ROTATE)
- Bug fixes for COUNTERMARCH (don't know of any, but they're probably
  there)
- Handle non-integer values
- FMMT (for FMTO NP; MTRM, we didn't decide on a name)
- improved scrolling
- improved selecting
- improved blockmove
- DOF, DOM, whatever we call them
- title bars reflecting show name
- fix sheet bar
- default name for new sheets
- automatically delete unused continuity
- finish autosave
- fix weirdness when drawing arc for Rotatemove
- Shearmove... any direction
- Display zero vector for Geniusmove
- Order of move icons
- fix undo set beats
- fix bug with large values of beats
- point variables... SPOT, VECTOR, etc.
- clear continuity text
- display sheet # in continuity window
- fix Dan's animation bug
- move Edit printed continuity menu item
- make EITHER take a direction
- fix EITHER with P
- more information error messages (line numbers, etc.)
- special cases of Geniusmove

There are a couple that I've fixed:

- Option to reset reference points
- Reprocess collisions after reanimating

Let me know about anything else.

